OL,3,COfcom announces 'game changing' new
OL,4,Crules to keep children safe online
OL,6,FResearch by Ofcom last year found that
OL,7,Fchildren aged eight to 17 spend
OL,8,Fbetween two and five hours online per
OL,9,Fday, and that amount of time increases
OL,10,Fwith age.
OL,12,FNearly every child over 12 has a
OL,13,Fmobile phone, and almost all of them
OL,14,Fwatch videos on platforms such as
OL,15,FYouTube or TikTok. Children aged five
OL,16,Fto seven are increasingly present
OL,17,Fonline, with a third found to use
OL,18,Fsocial media unsupervised.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/15
