OL,3,COfcom announces 'game changing' new
OL,4,Crules to keep children safe online
OL,6,F"We need to build on the momentum of
OL,7,Fthe Children's Code and demand bolder,
OL,8,Ffaster and more radical action so that
OL,9,Fevery child can grow up free from
OL,10,Faddictive design, toxic content and
OL,11,Fexploitative algorithms."
OL,13,FThe NSPCC, a charity safeguarding
OL,14,Fchildren in the UK, called Thursday's
OL,15,Fmeasures a "pivotal moment" - but also
OL,16,Fsaid the regulator must go further, as
OL,17,Funmoderated content and end-to-end
OL,18,Fencryption continue to pose risks.
